f to meet **48-hour advance notice** for data erasure (triggered via **CAI**).  \n\n---\n\n### 3. Data Security Measures (50% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** High  \n**Implications:** Lack of real-time monitoring increases breach risks.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Implement **real-time alerts** and anomaly detection.  \n2. **Informatica Solution:** Partner with **securiti.ai** for API threat monitoring.  \n\n---\n\n### 4. Data Breach Notification (0% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** Critical  \n**Implications:** Missed 72-hour reporting window may result in fines.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Revise breach templates to include **DPDP Section 7(1)(a)-(e)** details.  \n2. Automate breach detection and notification workflows.  \n\n---\n\n### 5. Data Retention & Erasure (25% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** High  \n**Implications:** Manual processes delay compliance with erasure requests.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. **Automate erasure** via **Informatica Cloud Data Integration**.  \n2. Ensure **48-hour customer notifications** before deletion.  \n\n---\n\n### 6. Cross-Border Data Transfers (16.7% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** Critical  \n**Implications:** Unauthorized transfers violate RBI/IRDAI localization norms.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Enforce **data residency compliance** using **Informatica region-specific processing**.  \n2. Block unauthorized transfers through policy controls.  \n\n---\n\n## Prioritized Action Plan  \n1. **Immediate (0–30 days):**  \n   - Deploy **Informatica Data Privacy Management** for principal rights.  \n   - Implement breach notification templates and workflows.  \n2. **Short-Term (30–90 days):**  \n   - Automate erasure and consent via **CDGC/CDAM**.  \n   - Strengthen third-party contracts with security clauses.  \n3. **Long-Term (90+ days):**  \n   - Conduct annual **DPIAs** and audits.  \n   - Enhance staff training on DPDP obligations.  \n\n---\n\n## Strategic Recommendations  \n- **Automate Compliance:** Use **Informatica solutions